1
00:00:16,277 --> 00:00:18,989
Everyone’s come to our house today,

2
00:00:18,989 --> 00:00:22,899
But no one is asking me if I can play.

3
00:00:22,899 --> 00:00:26,170
They’re all wearing suits and they’re all wearing black,

4
00:00:26,170 --> 00:00:31,995
Like a murder of crows in a big, noisy pack.

5
00:00:31,995 --> 00:00:35,426
There’s sausage rolls sitting on paper plates,

6
00:00:35,426 --> 00:00:39,573
And people keep talking about "the fates."

7
00:00:39,573 --> 00:00:42,845
The tea is too hot and the kitchen is loud,

8
00:00:42,845 --> 00:00:46,595
I’m looking for her in the middle of the crowd.

9
00:00:46,595 --> 00:00:50,585
But she isn't there in her favorite chair,

10
00:00:50,585 --> 00:00:55,341
She isn't upstairs brushing her hair.

11
00:00:55,691 --> 00:00:59,362
And there are black balloons tied to the garden gate,

12
00:00:59,362 --> 00:01:00,079
Is it a party?

13
00:01:00,079 --> 00:01:01,994
can just..

14
00:01:01,994 --> 00:01:03,829
someone tell me straight..

15
00:01:03,829 --> 00:01:06,781
Why is the balloon the color of night?

16
00:01:06,781 --> 00:01:11,409
When they say everything is "alright"?

17
00:01:11,409 --> 00:01:14,361
I don't really understand,

18
00:01:14,361 --> 00:01:17,871
"sweetheart" they say as they take my hand.

19
00:01:17,871 --> 00:01:18,829
Though we are here,

20
00:01:18,829 --> 00:01:19,468
my aunties,

21
00:01:19,468 --> 00:01:20,823
are left missing.

22
00:01:20,823 --> 00:01:22,659
just a little heart left wishin',

23
00:01:22,659 --> 00:01:23,456
they would be more,

24
00:01:23,456 --> 00:01:34,596
than dads stories.

25
00:01:34,947 --> 00:01:38,218
We went to the park where the grass was all wet,

26
00:01:38,218 --> 00:01:41,888
To a place I'm not likely to forget.

27
00:01:41,888 --> 00:01:45,638
There was a big wooden box with a shiny lid,

28
00:01:45,638 --> 00:01:48,750
I think, I was the only kid,

29
00:01:48,750 --> 00:01:49,867
there at all.

30
00:01:49,867 --> 00:01:51,063
Someone read

31
00:01:51,063 --> 00:01:52,978
She’s as big as the sky,

32
00:01:52,978 --> 00:01:55,052
she’s as big as it all.

33
00:01:55,052 --> 00:01:59,920
They lowered the box down with a rope and a prayer,

34
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:04,069
Two trumpets played some old fanfare.

35
00:02:04,069 --> 00:02:07,739
An old lady dressed in this guise,

36
00:02:07,739 --> 00:02:12,846
hiding well the tears in her eyes.

37
00:02:12,846 --> 00:02:14,681
I am not sure,

38
00:02:14,681 --> 00:02:20,186
what I am supposed to do.

39
00:02:20,186 --> 00:02:21,543
I am not sure,

40
00:02:21,543 --> 00:02:25,691
I have the slightest of a clue.

41
00:02:25,691 --> 00:02:26,489
But dad said,

42
00:02:26,489 --> 00:02:28,484
It's fine to not comprehend,

43
00:02:28,484 --> 00:02:33,590
It's okay to not pretend.

44
00:02:33,590 --> 00:02:35,903
If these balloons go pop,

45
00:02:35,903 --> 00:02:41,010
Will the rain in the living room finally stop?

46
00:02:41,010 --> 00:02:43,324
If I wear my red jumper,

47
00:02:43,324 --> 00:02:44,840
will I be in trouble?

48
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,754
It is very thin,

49
00:02:46,754 --> 00:02:48,590
this dark bubble.

50
00:02:48,590 --> 00:02:50,664
The man in with the collar said,

51
00:02:50,664 --> 00:02:52,580
she’s "in a better place".

52
00:02:52,580 --> 00:02:54,574
I saw not much on his face.

53
00:02:54,574 --> 00:02:56,250
Yeah, there are black balloons tied to the garden gate,

54
00:02:56,250 --> 00:03:05,105
I think I’m not the only one staying up late.

55
00:03:05,105 --> 00:03:08,936
Dad said it's kind of like a "celebration",

56
00:03:08,936 --> 00:03:12,846
but I've this odd sensation.

57
00:03:12,846 --> 00:03:16,995
a way we remember them for who they were,

58
00:03:16,995 --> 00:03:19,947
"this is something that must occur".

59
00:03:19,947 --> 00:03:22,020
And the truth is..

60
00:03:22,020 --> 00:03:24,096
I..

61
00:03:24,096 --> 00:03:27,127
I am not ready for any of this.

62
00:03:27,127 --> 00:03:29,760
There is more than I know,

63
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:36,462
That I will miss.

64
00:03:36,462 --> 00:03:55,691
Mum...

65
00:03:55,691 --> 00:03:55,711
I’m standing here,

66
00:03:55,691 --> 00:03:57,127
one by one I say goodbye.

67
00:03:57,127 --> 00:03:58,883
just me by the garden wall,

68
00:03:58,883 --> 00:04:03,111
The sun sets and the shadows loom tall.

69
00:04:03,111 --> 00:04:04,388
Maybe I should,

70
00:04:04,388 --> 00:04:05,903
I should,

71
00:04:05,903 --> 00:04:07,340
Shouldn't I..

72
00:04:07,340 --> 00:04:08,138
Aye,

73
00:04:08,138 --> 00:04:11,967
I'm going to give it a try..

74
00:04:11,967 --> 00:04:14,760
one by one I say goodbye.

75
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:15,798
Just..

76
00:04:15,798 --> 00:04:19,387
So you're not alone..

77
00:04:19,387 --> 00:04:20,266
Bye bye,

78
00:04:20,266 --> 00:04:20,952
little black balloon..
